<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 94 / World Stock Markets: Canada
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Toronto stocks opened higher but slid through the rest of the day to close
slightly lower. In a quiet session, the big losses were in heavily-weighted
golds and financial stocks.
The TSE 300 composite index was down 11.66 points, or 0.27 per cent, to
4,343.37, with losers ahead of winners by 410 to 353.
Volume of 71.06m shares was up from yesterday's 64.67m, while today's value
of CDollars 912.5m was slightly lower than Wednesday's CDollars 923.7m.
Overall, seven of the 14 sub-indexes were up, led by transportation, real
estate and pipelines. Golds - down 1.45 per cent - and oil and gas shares
posted the biggest losses.
</TEXT>
