<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 94 / World Stock Markets: Mexico
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Equities closed up 0.69 per cent, boosting the market by an accumulated 5.3
per cent over three consequetive days, with investors optimism high ahead of
third-quarter results.
The IPC index closed up 18.79 points at 2,759.61. Volume totaled a moderate
1.09bn new pesos on 80.6m shares traded.
There was good demand throughout the session as expectations mounted for
solid corporate earnings due before the month end.
Good results of Mexico's top financial concern, Grupo Financiero
Banamex-Accival, the first major company to report third-quarter earnings,
consolidated the market speculation about results in general.
</TEXT>
