FT  14 OCT 94 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Australian market hovered and tended a fraction easier in the first half
of the wool sales week, but subsequently began to show more strength, with
increases of 5-to 10 cents a kg. paid for some wools on the closing day.
This resulted in an Eastern states market indicator quotations of 738 cents
at the close, only one cent lower than a week before. China is reported to
have been a more active buyer of wool in Australia as the week progressed.
The view there is that this is the area where long-term demand will develop,
and after relatively subdued buying in the earlier weeks of the season price
rises could result from re-entry. Economic recovery and wool textile
activity combine to keep the background elsewhere sound, and a firmer
tendency after the recent world market setback could bring new orders
through, traders believe.
