<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 94 / International Company News: Threat to NRMA's ADollars 2.2bn
flotation
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BRUCE JACQUES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The proposed ADollars 2.2bn (USDollars 1.35bn) float of NRMA, the Australian
motorists' and insurance co-operative, has been thrown into doubt by a
Federal Court ruling yesterday, writes Bruce Jacques in Sydney.
The court ruled in Sydney that a meeting of NRMA members to vote on the
float, scheduled for October 19, should be postponed indefinitely. It also
banned the NRMA from distributing more float prospectuses, describing this
as 'conduct which is misleading or deceptive'.
The ruling followed an action brought by dissident NRMA directors who object
to directions on the matter will be issued on October 25. The NRMA said it
would consider an appeal.
