<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 94 / International Company News: Incentive plans to re-list part
of Cardo group
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BROWN-HUMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Incentive, the Swedish industrial and investment company controlled by the
Wallenberg family, plans to re-list part of the newly-acquired Cardo
investment group early next year, writes Christopher Brown-Humes in
Stockholm. Incentive bought Cardo for SKr8.4bn (Dollars 1.14bn) in May
because it wanted to acquire its controlling 58 per cent voting stake in the
medical equipment specialist Gambro. The new Cardo will comprise most of the
investment group's other industrial operations, based on doors, pumps and
railway breaking systems. It has manufacturing and sales companies in 21
countries and 5,600 employees. Sales in 1994 are projected to reach
SKr5.4bn.
Mr Lennart Nilsson, president of Cardo, said: 'The new Cardo is a
streamlined industrial group with strong market positions within its
respective product areas. This creates a favourable base for further
expansion.'
Holders of shares and warrants in the old Cardo will have preferential
rights to subscribe for shares in the new company, and will gain a discount.
Incentive said it may retain an ownership interest.
</TEXT>
