<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 94 / International Company News: Transocean secures fleet loan
refinancing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN FOSSLI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   OSLO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Transocean, the Norwegian drilling rig owner, has secured refinancing of its
fleet loans with an international syndicate of banks led by Den norske Bank
and Christiania Bank, Norway's two largest banks, writes Karen Fossli in
Oslo.
The Dollars 176m agreement is based on a five-year loan with an eight-year
repayment schedule and secures long-term financing for rig operations.
Transocean said the new repayment schedule had improved considerably,
reducing the group's average annual repayments to Dollars 21m a year from
Dollars 41m in 1995 and Dollars 82m in 1996.
In April, Transocean acquired Ross Offshore, a competitor - the refinancing
has allowed the two group's previous three loans to be incorporated into
one.
