<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Martin International
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Martin International, the clothing manufacturer and Marks and Spencer
supplier, plans to raise Pounds 5.9m through a rights issue and
subscription.
The fully underwritten rights issue of 12m new ordinary shares, on a 1-for-2
basis at 27p, will raise Pounds 2.9m net. A further Pounds 3m will be raised
through an issue of preference shares and warrants to Throgmorton Preferred
Income Trust. Proceeds will fund development and reduce core bank
borrowings.
The company also announced a turnround from pre-tax losses of Pounds 270,000
to profits of Pounds 267,000 for the first half of 1994. Turnover advanced
to Pounds 35.2m (Pounds 33.9m) including Pounds 569,000 (Pounds 1.53m) from
discontinued operations.
Earnings per share emerged at 0.8p (1.6p losses) and the interim dividend is
0.45p (0.4p). Directors expect to recommend a final of at least 0.65p. The
shares closed down 4 1/2 p at 30 1/2 p.
</TEXT>
