FT  14 OCT 94 / Faberge Imperial egg to be sold
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Winter Egg, one of Carl Faberge's Imperial Easter eggs, is to be offered
at auction at Christie's in Geneva on November 16.
The egg, a gift from Tsar Nicholas II to his mother, in 1913, is made of
rock crystal with a 'surprise' of a platinum basket and quartz anenomes, and
has more than 3,000 diamonds. It is expected to realise between Pounds 1.6m
and Pounds 3m.
