<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 94 / Finnish PM forecasts referendum Yes vote
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HELSINKI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The prime minister, Mr Esko Aho, says he expects Finns to vote for European
Union membership in their referendum on Sunday,
Recent opinion polls have shown Finns leaning strongly towards joining the
EU. Mr Aho, chairman of the agrarian-based Centre party, said there would be
some disadvantages to membership, like the impact on agriculture which must
adopt to much lower producer prices. 'And it is quite clear that sometimes
it is going to be difficult also to accept decisions not made at home,' Mr
Aho said in an interview. 'So it means that in certain way our independence
is going to be decreased.' Mr Aho, whose country shares a 1,270km border
with Russia, said he hoped Moscow would continue with reforms. Asked if
Finland would feel greater security in EU membership, he said: 'It is very
important to notice that we have no reason to see Russia as a military
threat.'
