<HEADLINE>
FT  13 OCT 94 / World Trade News: Intracom - Contracts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Our Foreign Staff
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LONDON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Intracom, the Greek telecommunications and information company, yesterday
signed a contract to modernise telephone communications at the Kremlin. The
one-year turn-key project involves installation of an AXE-10 Digital
Exchange. Intracom manufactures the AXE-10 under licence from Ericsson of
Sweden. Foreign Staff, London
