FT  13 OCT 94 / International Company News: Goodyear sees higher third-term
earnings
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Goodyear, the US tyre maker, said that it would report third-quarter
earnings of between 97 cents and Dollars 1 a share, a range which puts it in
line with most market forecasts, writes Richard Waters in New York.
Mr Stanley Gault, chairman, gave the projection in a speech to a meeting of
securities analysts yesterday. Sales for the period to the end of September
were more than 6 per cent up on the Dollars 2.9bn of the 1993 period, he
added.
The improvement in earnings per share, from 92 cents a year earlier, comes
against the background of rising rubber prices, which had threatened to put
pressure on margins.
Separately, Goodyear said it would acquire a 60 per cent interest in a
manufacturing joint venture with Quingdao Gold Lion Hose, the largest
producer of automotive hose in China. The total investment for the joint
venture is valued at Dollars 20m, of which 60 per cent will come from
Goodyear.
