FT  13 OCT 94 / International Company News: Taiwan banks ahead
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Our Financial Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Taiwan's big three state-run commercial banks have all reported higher
pre-tax profits for the July-September quarter compared with a year ago,
writes Our Financial Staff.
At Hua Nan Bank, pre-tax profits rose to TDollars 2.12bn (USDollars 80m)
from TDollars 1.38bn on turnover of TDollars 15.17bn, compared with TDollars
13.53bn last time. First Commercial Bank turnover rose more modestly to
TDollars 15.54bn from TDollars 14.78bn. but pre-tax profits leapt to
TDollars 2.01bn from TDollars 1.57bn. At Chang Hwa Bank, pre-tax profits
advanced to TDollars 1.50bn from TDollars 1.23bn a year ago. Revenues were
not reported.
